def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # NOTE: This doesn't deal with hierarchical columns yet

    index = data.index

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    clevels = [index.levels[i] for i in clocs]
    ccodes = [index.codes[i] for i in clocs]
    cnames = [index.names[i] for i in clocs]
    rlevels = [index.levels[i] for i in rlocs]
    rcodes = [index.codes[i] for i in rlocs]
    rnames = [index.names[i] for i in rlocs]

    shape = [len(x) for x in clevels]
    group_index = get_group_index(ccodes, shape, sort=False, xnull=False)

    comp_ids, obs_ids = compress_group_index(group_index, sort=False)
    recons_codes = decons_obs_group_ids(comp_ids, obs_ids, shape, ccodes, xnull=False)

    # Define the dummy index based on the remaining levels that are not unstacked
    dummy_index_names = [rnames] + [obs_ids]
    dummy_index = MultiIndex(levels=rlevels + [obs_ids], codes=rcodes + [comp_ids], names=rnames + ["__placeholder__"], verify_integrity=False)

    # If the input data is a Series, unstack it directly
    if isinstance(data, Series):
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index
        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
        new_levels = clevels + [dummy_index.levels[0]]
        new_names = cnames + [data.name]
        new_codes = recons_codes + [unstacked.columns.codes[-1]]

    # If the input data is a DataFrame, unstack each level in clocs iteratively
    else:
        result = data
        for i in range(len(clocs)):
            val = clocs[i]
            result = result.unstack(val, fill_value=fill_value)
            # Update the levels index when unstacking each level in clocs
            new_levels = [result.columns.levels[1]] + clevels
            new_names = [data.columns.name] + cnames
            new_codes = [result.columns.codes[0]]
            for rec in recons_codes:
                new_codes.append(rec.take(result.columns.codes[-1]))

    new_columns = MultiIndex(levels=new_levels, codes=new_codes, names=new_names, verify_integrity=False)

    # Update the index or columns of the unstacked result based on whether the input data was a Series or a DataFrame
    if isinstance(result, Series):
        result.index = new_columns
    else:
        result.columns = new_columns

    return result
